profile_positions.description:
SwanWaters.com is an online support community for survivors on non-physical domestic abuse. I am one of the co-founders and my work includes:

• Writing and editing resources to support survivors on their healing journey;
• Streamlining communications with team members and service providers;
• Managing communication and marketing through social media, newsletters, and content creation;
• Community management and support of members;
• Creating original graphics, illustrations, and publications.

CBI is an agency of the Ministry of Finance (formerly Ministry of Foreign Affairs), that works for private sector development in developing countries. Tasks included:

• Administration of various projects, and these were handled in compliance with procedural requirements;
• Making arrangements for training seminars in the Netherlands and abroad;
• Liaising with partner organisations, external sector experts, and programme participants;
• Drafting contracts for suppliers.

Additionally I worked on several projects:

• Recording of work processes and development of training materials for (new) staff members.
• Automating registration processes for participants.
• Editing English texts, such as brochures and subtitles for corporate films.
• I was also elected to the works council in the last year of my employment.
